# Convert tooling

- Convert CLI is the published package `@dukk/doc-repo-convert` ([doc-repo-tools](https://github.com/dukk/doc-repo-tools)); do not reintroduce an in-repo `tools/convert` copy.
- Keep Pandoc as the conversion engine; do not add a parallel export stack without a clear need.
- Supported formats remain `pdf`, `docx`, `html`, `pptx`.
- Convert **document packages** (`convert.yaml` + Markdown sources); skip reserved `index.md` / `log.md`.
- Honor `convert.yaml` for out/formats/documents/sources/assets/links/options/metadata; CLI `--format` / `--out` override when provided.
- For DOCX/PPTX styling, headers, and footers, prefer `options.reference_doc` (usually the package `.original/*.docx`) over inventing styles in Markdown.
- `options.cover_page: true` should emit a title page with a page break, not only a heading.
- Prepare image/Mermaid artifacts before Pandoc when `assets.mode: generate`.
- Rewrite Markdown links according to `links.markdown` using the output manifest.
- Map OKF frontmatter into Pandoc metadata; merge package + document-group metadata on top.
- Document system dependencies (Pandoc, Mermaid CLI, PDF engine) in the root README and the convert package README.
